file=Engineering/axiom/custom/performance-profiling/assets/benchmark-record-template.md · br—:Benchmark Record — [what was measured] — [date]=> Measure before and after; keep only measured wins. Numbers make performance claims real (rule 0.6). Profiler per stack-profile.\n · w(b:Workload (must be realistic + recorded for comparability)=- Input size n: [value — should resemble production regime]\n- Distribution / shape: [uniform / skewed / worst-case / production sample]\n- Environment: [machine class / container / conditions]\n- Profiler: [tool per stack-profile]\n · hs:Hot spot=- Location: [file:function]\n- Type: [algorithmic → complexity-analysis / constant-factor → implementation]\n · c(t:Change (one thing, for an attributable delta)=- [description]\n · tb=\| metric \| before \| after \| delta \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| [latency p50/p95 / throughput / allocations / cpu] \| \| \| [%/x] \| · r:Result=- Within run-to-run noise? [yes → treat as no improvement] / [no]\n- **Verdict:** KEEP / REVERT (no measured improvement = revert)\n · f:Feeds=- ops baseline update? [ref] \· dsa-design-record trade-off backed? [DSR-ref]\n